🪴 How can we grow more into our divine nature of compassion? 

👁️ Seek wisdom - Create an intention to do this and your reality will expand to be more open to perspectives outside of your own. 

This is not to say all perspectives will resonate, yet instead that even if someone else’s perspective is vastly different, the wisdom in that is showing you what you do prefer through contrast rather than getting caught up in who’s right/wrong or what’s good/bad. 

I find that being more open to listening to someone’s perspective allows me to be more of a compassionate human. 

Boundaries are healthy and so are our preferences, yet allowing someone an opportunity to share their personal reality opens many doors that would otherwise be closed off. 

🙏🏼What wisdom have you gained from being open to another’s unique perspective?

🥶 What is your process for cold plunging ? 

🔥 One of my favorite things to do immediately post plunge at @optimyze.me is a 5 minute wall sit.  By choosing to do this movement immediately post cold, my body has to utilize its internal heating mechanism (metabolism) to turn on and fire up the muscles that allow for this exercise to be performed. 

💪🏽The 5 minute wall sit is something I do daily as a part of my strength routine amd doing it daily allows me to see how nourished, rested and recovered I am from day to day. 

Some days I get out of position 6-7 times in 5 minutes, other days I can hold without breaking position or only 1-2 times which is what I typically see after cold plunging. 

🙌🏽Movement is important after cold to allow your body to do what it can to bring you back into homeostasis or balance. 

💪🏽 What are your favorite post plunge movements?

🙏🏼How would  you like to feel more at peace more often ?
 
👁️ one of the ways we can do that is to 
practice being the witness, and letting go of being the judge. 

🤔 What does that mean? Being the judge means as soon as we experience somethings see someone think some thing often times we’re attaching a meaning to it whether it’s good or bad right wrong, awesome or stupid. There’s a constant dialogue going on when the judge of the inner critic is happening. 

We can notice this, either in how we judge others or more often we’re probably judging ourselves without even knowing it because that’s where it starts 

👍🏼there’s a difference between judgment and discernment 
Discernment is healthy and about the power of choice and preference. It just means something either resonates with the core of who you are and your values and judgment means you’re assigning a meaning to it. There’s an attachment there’s a separation that makes you either superior or inferior. 

When we judge it’s part of human nature as it’s tied into our ego the part of our self that does feel separate I believe, but it can also be Tamed with practice. 

🤔 Why would we want to be more of the witness and observer because in a neutral state we can experience more peace. Our nervous system can relax our hormones can balance. 

✌🏽 We bring more peace wherever we go when we are neutral people can feel the energy of judgment and it makes people feel very uncomfortable and chances are you may not even realize that it is disrupting something inside of you as well because that thing that is happening is creating separation and if we know that we are all unified through our creator God  then we understand why that is hurtful to us, as well as the other.

🤯With all the information there is out there it can be really confusing for someone just getting started on their health journey. 

💥we get bombarded with ads of this supplement and diet and that exercise program, different types of meditation etc which may work great for one person but you never know if it’s for you.

🧩 Whether you are returning from an injury, you’ve been traveling a lot and overworking without prioritizing your health, or you’re coming out of rehab and you’re in the process of maintaining recovery from an addiction, The key is to start with simple habits each week and build upon them. 

🙌🏽Here is an example of a small start that could have a profound impact on your health starting with five minutes of breath work, eliminating something from your eating regimen, adding nutrient dense foods  and moving more. 

☑️ once you get started, take inventory of how you feel each time you commit to the small habits. It’s also helpful to hire an accountability coach whether that’s a fitness coach a life coach or a therapist someone who can hold you accountable for these actions you’d like to implement in your new lifestyle.

🩷Through holistic wellness coaching I help people assess where they need to make changes in their habits and lifestyle in order to get the results they want to achieve that allows them to feel amazing inside and out. 

✋🏼Who’s ready to commit to small impactful daily habits to create lasting change NOW?

🧠 Our mind can choose many different possibilities when faced with a challenging situation. 

👁️ When we’re going through something tough sometimes it’s hard to see any other possibility besides a hopeless one. 

🙌🏽in my experience it has helped me to see other people who have been through similar things who are now thriving. People who refuse to live as a victim of circumstance and take charge of their mental, emotional, and spiritual wellbeing as best as they can. 

📺 It’s like watching the movie miracle man where the guy gets in an airplane accident is Completely paralyzed, and eventually is so inspired to move his body and prove doctors wrong that by the end of the movie he is walking out  on his two feet to the doctors amazement. 

🫶🏼👁️seeing things like the shows us of the possibilities. It’s not denial to think about the other possibilities or toxic positive thinking, it’s simply seeing what’s possible and allowing our mind to go there to focus. 

🙏🏼If there’s something you’re experiencing, whether it’s being an addict, seeing other addicts, get clean, being diagnosed with something and seeing other people overcome that or live in an empowered state even with that condition, it really does help the mind when we see other people doing empowering things. 

✨✨. please share any inspiring book, movie, podcast, person who has helped YOU to see the possibilities! 

#mindset #possibilities #empowerment

⛰️What is your highest intention? 

Knowing this allows us when faced with discomfort to practice, maintaining our will to stay aligned with our intention. 

The moment we lose sight of the intention - when we make excuses, when we let a craving get the best of us, when we feel justified and lose our power over it and our willpower (the force that carries out the intention ) takes us in another direction. That means that intention wasn’t strong enough in that moment.

By having a true North, or knowing our highest intention, it’s a lot easier for us to know what we NEED to do in each moment. Life’s practice will throw things at us to try to deter us yet the more we keep our focus on that intention, the more we will take the divine path for our souls evolution.

👗🤍Do you remember the phenomenon a few years back about “the dress is black and blue, or the dress is gold and yellow?” 
Or the word is “Laurel or Yanny?” 

These seemingly silly phenomenon led us to greater  awareness that 2 people can look at the same thing & be absolutely certain about what they see & what is the truth. 

I thought of this recently, as I’ve experienced a few times w/ people very close to me, seeing the same situation/thing completely differently & that causing tension until we can commit to a higher intention of staying connected even amongst different beliefs about our experience. We have the right to our perceptions likely based on our beliefs systems,life experiences, & values. 

I thought of this not only on the micro scale of interpersonal relationships but also the macro scale of global relationships & some of the turmoil in the world, the disagreements & why we can’t see eye to eye sometimes. 

When we see specific things so differently, how can we find common ground? 

This is important in establishing peace in the world. It starts w/in ourselves, then w/in our closest relationships.

👁️ We can seek to understand 1st where we find turmoil & conflict within ourself. That’s the most important thing to address, as if we feel conflicted within ourselves,  how can we feel harmony w/ other people?  Determining our highest values will help us understand how to navigate the conflict within ourselves & sometimes our values shift overtime so we need to continue to reassess that in order to find peace within.

🤍Next in our closest relationships, where do we feel a lack of harmony and how can we have deeper communication and set intentions to find common ground of mutual respect, honor, and the intention to stay connected throughout disagreements? 

🙏🏼From our closest relationships, moving  further out into our community and then into our country, globally and Universally. We’re all connected so it’s important that we establish that connection within and the harmony in order to experience it without. 

This is a great reminder of the quote “As above so below as within so without.”

🤔 what action can you take to establish more peace within?

👁️ See Through the Filter of Compassion

👁️How often in life are we looking at things (people, circumstances, events,) through the eyes of a particular filter?  The filter of conditioning, past experiences, judgement,a closed mind, a limited belief, the filter of stubbornness & righteousness, w/ a lack of willingness to see another’s perspective because we’re so attached to our own reality being right/correct? 

💟Do we say we’re compassionate yet the compassion has limitations and conditions? 
🤔 What decides in you who deserves it and what decides who doesn’t? 
👼🏽If we all started in this world as an infant we know we’ve been conditioned from day one. 

🙏🏼Wouldn’t this mean that we know that ultimately we’re dealing w/ conditioning, egos & personalities of people not necessarily their souls/spirits? 

🫵🏻If we want to break dysfunctional patterns We need to take Personal responsibility to do something about what’s not working in our lives rather than blame someone for our issues. 

🙏🏼Sometimes I see people who have had horrible circumstances make the most massive amount of change & while we commend that & it’s amazing & miraculous for sure, how do we know that somebody  w/ “less of a story” doesn’t have a limited capacity based on intense conditioning. They may be seemingly capable, but yet their actions are not showing they are so let us have compassion on that too! 

🙌🏽Compassion isn’t an excuse poor behavior, instead it’s an opportunity to extend love - (with healthy boundaries) rather than hate/judgement.We can seek to recognize that someone isn’t operating w/ fullest capacity mentally emotionally physically & spiritually otherwise they’d show up differently so we can let go of judgments & assumptions about people, how they should behave & show up & if they deserve compassion or not. It blows me away. 
💟I myself am evolving in compassion even though it’s a gift that comes easily to me. I have tremendous empathy for people, but I recognize not everyone has this and this is why I speak on it often because I share my process for how I come to this way of being, feeling, & seeing the world. 

👁️let us learn to see through the filter of compassion.

🦶 There was a time I believed that I’d need orthotics for the rest of my life. I had worn them for 8 yrs after being told I needed them when I had chronic Achilles tendinitis  in 2012 & sought treatment. 
⚠️Disclaimer: I ❤️ physical therapists! I know there are many different schools of thought, & this may not be for everyone - I’m not saying orthotics are bad I just am sharing my own testimony in case somebody feels the same way & wants to explore other options.
👞 wearing orthotics worked until it didn’t. I was having some issues in my feet & calves that led me to seek physical therapy a few yrs ago. That particular physical therapist saw me wearing @xeroshoes and we talked about my footwear and my orthotics. I loved Xero shoes but I didn’t think I was able to wear them as much as I wear them now, because of what I was told about needing orthotics. 
👁️She empowered me to think differently. And this is the whole mission of Xero the company to #livefeetfirst. 

🏃🏼‍♀️ The volume of training that I was doing was too much for my feet being not strong enough for that much load in volume of training. 
🙏🏼When I surrendered to being patient in my journey of transitioning out of orthotics, I realized that I needed to back off on training that my feet were not strong enough yet for running so I did not run for a while. 
⏱️ Eventually over time oscillating back-&-forth between Xeros & orthotics, lessening the amount of time I was in orthotics & increasing the amt of time I was in the Xeros. 💪🏽 Eventually, I was able to strengthen my feet enough to run again, & also wear Xero shoes most of the day without my feet hurting or any other problems with feet calves/ankles. 
🙌🏽I highly recommend Xero shoes, because they allow me to ground and connect, it improves my entire strength and kinetic flow in my body bc now my feet are involved in training, rather than just being in an orthotic and relying on them as a brace which weakens the foot.

🌱 Growing in compassion is one of my missions to share. We could all use more compassion in this world with our fellow humans. 
❓Take a moment to ask yourself if there are some people you feel deserve more compassion than others. Likely you’ll feel that it’s easier to extend compassion to someone who is disempowered & struggling (fawn/freeze) than it is to someone whose response to life also trauma related is defensive /entitled ,even aggressive(fight/flight). Both types of people deserve the same level of compassion. 
☑️ 2 things to remember w/ compassion.:
1. Understand what compassion means because that word can be misinterpreted or misunderstood to mean that we tolerate/excuse/allow poor treatment from the others & that we need to stick around when things are not healthy. 
⚠️ It is quite the opposite because we must have boundaries when we’re extending compassion.The boundaries mean that if it’s unhealthy to continue in a relationship /communicate w/ people who are unhealthy, we will remove ourselves from that. Instead, it’s the ENERGY we’re sending out to the other person that can shift . 

For example, think of 2 people. 1 is a person on the street, who seems lost & disempowered their scars are visible, & you really feel for them. The 2nd person is a person who butts in line, and is unkind to the clerk at the counter, & seems very entitled & combative . We would probably find it easier to extend compassion to the person on the street than we would the seemingly functional entitled person. 
👋🏻 the reality is both are responding to their traumas in different ways (unconsciously) & both deserve more love not less love.
🙏🏼what compassion would be, is an ENERGETIC blessing toward the people who are either suffering & disempowered, or entitled & aggressive, sending that blessing rather than sending judgment,& deciding who deserves more compassion than the other. 
❤️let us set our intention today to grow in compassion sending love to everyone equally, even if we don’t agree with or understand their response. 
🌱May we all grow in consciousness and reprogram to respond with love. #compassion

🔥Not all stress is detrimental to health. In fact, I’m a firm believer in exposing yourself to controlled stress in forms of exercise, therapy, or doing things that allow you to practice calming your nervous system during stress like cold plunging and adventure sports i.e. running down a mountain ⛰️ 🏃🏽 

⛔️ it is chronic stress that’s the silent killer and we need to stop normalizing that as if it’s a badge of honor and recognize that it’s time to take action when we start to see the symptoms of chronic stress which can include things like :

Inability to sleep 
Digestive issues 
Skin issues 
Difficulty in concentrating 
Lack of patience 
Hormone imbalances
And the list goes on ..

😬 if you’re like many people, you probably are experiencing chronic stress either from work, relationship, or any other situation That might be stressful over an extended period of time.  Those symptoms are a warning sign to do something different or else !!

⏲️NOW is the time to take action. I spoke on letting go of all or nothing mentality and even though for example, going to bed 30 min earlier, doing three minutes of breath work, meditating 5 min in the am , or walking a mile a day can seem minuscule in comparison to your level of chronic stress, doing those simple things daily will start to have a positive impact and compounding effects.

🆕 Foam Roll Mobility Series:  Psoas / Hip Flexors 

🪑 extended periods of sitting shorten or hip flexors or psoas. Also, standing with an anterior tilt in the pelvis, (which many people experience) shortens the hip flexors. 

☝🏼When this happens, glutes become weaker and hips become tighter and weaker as well. 

⚖️ There needs to be a balance between hip flexors and glute strength, and by activating the glutes in this stretch, it allows the brain to connect with both lengthening and strengthening at the same time.

💪🏽 Rather than just being passive in stretches, I like to activate my opposing muscle-glute in this particular stretch, I am contracting the glutes as the hip is opening. 

⚠️ be gentle with the stretch as your hips may be very tight.

🆕 Core Series: Towel Pelvic Tilts

💪🏽A strong and stable core creates foundational strength that connects the entire body. 

⚠️ when the core is weak and unstable that sets a person up for risk of injury, a tight low back and dysfunctional movement patterns. 

💡 Knowing how to properly engage the core is important in all activities and often times when we haven’t practiced engaging the core it becomes weak and unstable creating dysfunction across the entire body. 

🙌🏽One of the most fundamental movements to master is the ability to find and maintain a neutral spine as well as activating the internal weight belt otherwise known as the TVA - Transverse Abdominals while at the same time activating the pelvic floor (muscles that help with going to the bathroom and staying dry while jumping etc) 

💥 This simple yet profound exercise will help your brain reconnect with the areas of the body- that when moving or standing are not getting activated for some. By practicing in small simple ways it can and should translate to activation during movement. 

🤔 have you tried this move? If so, how helpful has it been in engaging your core?

🆕 Core Series: Glute Bridge + Med Ball Adduction

🙌🏽Part of having a strong core involves glutes that can assist in maintaining a neutral spine. 

💯Glute bridges allow for proper activation of the glutes while adduction assists in hip stabilization. 

⚖️ Beyond the desired aesthetics of having great glutes the functionality piece is far superior in its ability to maintain proper kinetic flow reducing the risk for injury and dysfunction. 

✅This exercise can be done daily to activate the glutes. Be sure the ball is small 4-6lb med ball and reps can range from 10-50 depending on your fitness level.

⚖️ Topic: Creating Balance in Unstable Environments

🥵 What are Electrolytes and why are they important when we sauna? 

Electrolytes are minerals in your body that have an electric charge. They are found in your blood, urine, tissues, and other body fluids. The most common electrolytes are sodium, potassium, calcium, bicarbonate, magnesium, chloride, and phosphate.

Why are They Important?
Electrolytes are essential for a multitude of body functions. They help:

	•	Balance the amount of water in your body.
	•	Balance your body’s acid/base (pH) level.
	•	Move nutrients into your cells.
	•	Move wastes out of your cells.
	•	Ensure that your nerves, muscles, heart, and brain work the way they should.

Electrolytes and Hydration 💧 

When you’re hydrated, your body has the right balance of electrolytes. But when you lose fluids (through sweating, especially during exercise, or when you’re using sauna ), you also lose electrolytes. That’s why drinking water isn’t always enough for hydration, especially after intense physical activity or in hot weather. You need to replenish your electrolytes as well.

Natural Sources of Electrolytes 🥥 

You can replenish electrolytes through your diet. Some electrolyte-rich foods include bananas, spinach, potatoes, beans, avocados, oranges, and coconut water.

A Balanced Approach
Remember, while it’s important to replace lost electrolytes, it’s also crucial not to consume them in excess. We use products like @drinklmnt and @waterandwellnessco and @perfectamino all available at @optimyze.me
